        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 3:25PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 325 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aberdeen, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aberdeen, Warner, Bath, Columbia, Putney, and Tacoma Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
northeastern South Dakota.</instruction>
